## TL;DR: What Every 3ct Emerald Cut Buyer Must Know

A 3 carat emerald cut diamond ring exists in two completely different price worlds depending on whether you buy natural or lab-grown.

**Natural 3ct emerald cut ring:** The [GIA 3.09ct F-VS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/15813280?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs $63,574 for the stone alone. Add the [Riviera Pavé WG setting at $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-diamond-band-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and your total ring is **$65,089**.

**Lab 3ct emerald cut ring:** The [IGI 3ct D-IF Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28885081?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs $9,235 for the stone. Same setting, total ring is **$10,750**. The lab stone has higher colour (D vs F) and higher clarity (IF vs VS1) — and costs $54,339 less.

**One more thing.** A [lab 4ct D-VVS1](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29587315?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in the same setting totals **$9,252** — less than the lab 3ct, more stone. If you're buying lab, 4ct may be the better decision than 3ct.

→ **Best total ring under $11,000.** [IGI 3ct D-IF Ideal lab emerald cut at $9,235](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28885081?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) + [Riviera Pavé WG $1,515](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/riviera-pave-diamond-band-engagement-ring-in-18k-white-gold-item-195326?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) = **$10,750 total.** Three carats of certified lab diamond, D colour, Internally Flawless. The best 3ct emerald cut ring in the market right now.

**Priority:** At 3ct, the stone IS the decision. This size is where the hall-of-mirrors effect becomes fully dramatic. VS1 clarity is non-negotiable. And if you're going lab, check whether a 4ct at lower total cost makes more sense than 3ct before you buy.

