## What Is a 3 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring?

A 3 carat emerald cut diamond ring centres a 3ct rectangular step-cut diamond — approximately 9.5mm × 6.7mm face-up — in an engagement or statement ring setting. At 3ct, the emerald cut is visually unmistakable. The hall-of-mirrors effect operates at full scale. The long mirrored facets read from across a room.

I'm **Farzana Hasan**, a GIA Expert. The [3 carat emerald cut diamond ring](/emerald-cut-diamond) is the purchase where the natural versus lab decision matters most. At 1ct, the price gap is manageable. At 3ct, the natural price is $63,000+ and the lab price is $10,000. That gap changes the entire decision.

Most buyers searching for a 3ct emerald cut ring start with two questions. How much does it cost? And how big does it look on the finger? This guide answers both — and shows you why 3ct lab is one of the best diamond purchases available at any price point.

Full credentials and methodology at **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**.

