## The 3-Carat Cliff

Natural emerald cut diamond pricing does not scale linearly with carat weight. It jumps.

[![Emerald cut diamond solitaire engagement ring in white gold on white background](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/BrioPackshotBox/Rings/505033/505033_M1_EMR_DIM_wht_0100CT_W_Box4_004_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?MetalType=all&Diamonds=Dia&ShapeID=Emerald&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

Look at the natural price progression in certified market inventory:
- 1ct GIA D-VS1 Ideal: **[$3,140](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29333987?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 1.5ct GIA E-VS1 Ideal: **[$10,409](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 2ct GIA F-VS1 Ideal: **[$24,407](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-search?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 3ct GIA F-VS1 Ideal: **[$63,574](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/15813280?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

From 2ct to 3ct natural — same F-VS1 GIA quality — the price jumps $39,167. That is a 160% price increase for one additional carat.

That jump is The 3-Carat Cliff.

**Why does The 3-Carat Cliff exist?** Three reasons. First, rough crystal material large enough to yield a 3ct emerald cut with VS1+ clarity is genuinely scarce. The emerald cut requires clean rough with minimal inclusions — step-cut facets expose everything. Finding clean 3ct+ rough is rare. Second, the emerald cut wastes more rough material than brilliant cuts do. The precise rectangular geometry means more of the rough ends up as polishing dust. Third, 3ct is a psychological threshold. Buyers pay a premium to cross it. Supply is scarce, demand has a premium, price reflects both.

**The natural 3ct buyer.** Natural 3ct emerald cuts are not retail purchases in the normal sense. They are collector-level acquisitions. A $65,089 ring is a significant wealth allocation, not a typical engagement ring budget. The buyers who choose natural at 3ct are doing so for specific reasons: provenance matters to them, resale value matters to them, or the natural rarity is part of the meaning of the purchase.

If none of those reasons apply to you — if what you want is the stone on the finger and the look it creates — the lab market answers The 3-Carat Cliff completely.

